Date: 0/0/1958
Source: Sheep.  Part 1, Sheep husbandry
Author: STEVENS
Vol / Page: 142
Edition:
Quote: White muscle disease or stiff lamb disease. The first signs shown by lambs are stiffness of the muscles and difficulty in walking - hence the name stiff lamb disease.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1959
Source: NZ Farmers' Veterinary Guide
Author: EDGAR
Vol / Page: 163
Edition:
Quote: White muscle disease (Crutching Cramp, Stiff Lamb disease.) A disease of lambs and hoggets which have been wintering on turnips.
